description.plain:
Brett Ryan Eldredge was born on March 23, 1986 in Paris, Illinois.  He is the son of Chris and Robin Beth Vonderlage Eldredge.  He is a country music singer and songwriter.  Besides vocals, he plays the guitar.

Songs that Brett is known for include “Don’t Ya” and “Lose My Mind”.

description.plain:
“Somethin' I’m Good At” is a song co-written and recorded by American country music artist Brett Eldredge. It was co-written with Tom Douglas and released on February 24, 2017 as the lead single from Eldredge’s self-titled fourth studio album.

The song was written in an hour after a five-hour session in which Eldredge worked on a ballad, and was recorded out of a desire to be spontaneous and have fun. Eldredge said of the song: “It made us write one of the craziest, out of nowhere fun songs I’ve ever written. I’ve never had so much fun recording.” His ad libs and laughter were left on the final recording. Douglas and producer Ross Copperman also provided backing vocals.

description.plain:
The second single released from Brett’s sophomore album Illinois.  It peaked at #2 on Both the Billboard Hot Country Songs charts and for Country Airplay. Becoming his fifth top ten hit on both of the charts.

The video for the song was inspired by a  1996 comedy film called Multiplicity. In the video (just like the movie) Brett plays multiple versions of himself each with a different personality. One of the people in the video is his older brother Brice.
